        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Soften the vegetables",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Heat the oil in a wide, deep saucepan over a medium heat. Add the onion, carrot, and celery and cook, ",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": []
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "sweating",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "termId": "cmpqyw15m0000k4v4uibyfs9i"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " them for 8 to 10 minutes until soft and lightly golden. Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute more.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Brown the mince and build the sauce",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Raise the heat to high. Add the beef mince and break it up with a wooden spoon. Cook without stirring too often so it browns rather than steams, about 5 minutes.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the tomato puree and stir for 1 minute. Pour in the tinned tomatoes and crush them with the spoon. Add the stock, oregano, and bay leaves. Season with salt and pepper.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, partially covered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally, until the sauce is thick and dark. Remove the bay leaves.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Cook the pasta and serve",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Bring a large pot of well-salted water to the boil. Cook the spaghetti until just tender, following the packet instructions. Reserve a mug of the cooking water before draining.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Drain the pasta and add it directly to the sauce. Toss to coat, adding a splash of pasta water if the sauce looks too thick. Serve with grated parmesan.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Remove the lid completely and simmer at a higher heat for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring often, until the sauce is thick. Only add pasta once the sauce is right.",
                "cause": "The mince released a lot of moisture and the sauce didn't reduce enough.",
                "symptom": "The sauce is watery"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Cook in smaller batches over a higher heat next time. Once it's in the sauce and simmered for an hour, the colour matters less to the final taste.",
                "cause": "Too much mince was added to the pan at once, or the heat was too low.",
                "symptom": "The mince is grey, not brown"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Continue simmering. A pinch of sugar can help in an emergency, but more time is the reliable fix.",
                "cause": "The tinned tomatoes were not cooked long enough to sweeten.",
                "symptom": "The sauce tastes acidic"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Add pasta to sauce as soon as it is drained. Reserve pasta water to loosen if needed.",
                "cause": "The pasta was drained and left to sit before being added to the sauce.",
                "symptom": "The pasta is clumped together"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Spaghetti bolognese arrived in British homes during the 1960s and 1970s. It was not quite Italian food. British bolognese used tinned tomatoes and a simple mince sauce, and it suited the national preference for food that was filling and easy to make. In most British households it became the dish children asked for most.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
